post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Optimal treatment of addiction sometimes means [needing to taper off](https://www.therecoveryvillage.com/heroin-addiction/heroin-taper/) a drug, however, under prohibition quitting "cold turkey" is the only legal option. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help patients by facilitating access to medicines \\(drugs\\) that are currently hard to obtain. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This could lead individuals into a false sense of safety when it comes to drug use.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Psychosis](https://www.earlypsychosis.ca/pages/curious/concerned-safety) can cause the sufferer to carry out self-harm or, in severe cases, suicide. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The drug industry, like alcohol and tobacco, can be heavily taxed, generating high revenues. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Suicide rates may increase as overdose will be an easily accessible option.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Education and information might not be enough to ensure thoughtful drug use.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The effects of smoking are slow and not always visible; this means people are not as aware of them.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs hinders scientific and, in particular, medical progress.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Rational discussion of the costs and benefits of smoking tobacco and negative ads led a lot of people to decide it isn't worth doing. All without prohibiting it."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The [majority](http://www.independent.co.uk/news/habits-most-drug-users-are-happy-successful-people-with-a-taste-for-the-good-life-1292155.html) of young individuals consuming illegal substances lead fulfilling and successful lives.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Since adults would prefer the legal market, these people would have to base their entire business on selling to underaged people. This would make it drastically less profitable, as well as easier to expose by police.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will remove the taboo that drug addiction currently carries with it. As a result, addicts will no longer be a target of prejudice. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[In 2017](https://www.kialo.com/all-drugs-should-be-legalized-7100/7100.0=7100.1+7100.297), there were more direct deaths from alcohol consumption than from drug consumption.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If drugs other than alcohol were legalized, alcohol sales would plummet, and a lot of jobs in the alcohol industry would disappear.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the same way that people sign contracts in which they voluntarily limit their freedom for a certain amount of time, a person who chooses freely to take drugs is choosing to limit their self-control freely. In either case, the initial choice is still a free choice. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Although social prejudice may remain, addicts could seek help far easier if there were no fear of legal repercussions.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This limits what we know about these compounds as well as to what length we are able to develop treatments for those struggling with addiction \\(physical and mental\\) as well as treatment for acute toxicity.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many users currently do not properly dispose of their paraphernalia for fear of being caught with it on them, leading to evidence of illegal drug use being disposed of quickly and carelessly.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'When the government legalizes something, it \\(unintentionally\\) sends the message that the substance is acceptable and a legitimate form of recreation. This may encourage people to become involved in drug taking.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Producers and distributors are not able to control how consumers use their products. Therefore, legalising the sale and possession of drugs necessarily would allow for this kind of abuse to increase easily despite the illegality of forcing another person to ingest them.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug cartels destabilize Latin America. With legalization they would disappear and Latin America would gain stability.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Criminals are not interested in drugs, their core interest is money. To gain the largest amount of money, in the quickest time, with the least effort, is their ultimate goal. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The government specifies what is unacceptable through prohibition. Taxation is how the government discourages. The government is only "encouraging" if they provide aid or assistance.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There is no guarantee that a similar legal compound will act the same way as the original one.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "A parent's drugs addiction can cause a child to suffer emotional harm and a lack of future stability as it can reduce the parent's life expectancy, causing them to die young. So drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Without help some conditions could [worsen](https://deserthopetreatment.com/co-occurring-disorders/going-untreated/) to the point where they're a danger to others. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Removing some of these constraints through the legalisation of drugs could make studies more successful.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The responsible use of drugs for recreational purposes does not harm others and therefore can not be considered immoral. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legal drugs would not be the only option; there may still be a market of illegal drugs, for example if it is cheaper than the legal choice.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Alcohol-dependent persons](https://academic.oup.com/alcalc/article/46/2/105/198339) have to face prejudices, although the substance is legal: They are often held responsible for their condition, are subject to social rejection and they are at particular risk for structural discrimination.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will allow governments to fight addictive drugs more effectively. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use negatively affects job performance.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Just because there are other systematic racial issues does not mean we cannot challenge this particular racist law.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Cocaine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug_harmfulness#/media/File:HarmCausedByDrugsTable.svg) is less harmful than alcohol, and only slightly more addictive. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalisation of drugs allows for them to be regulated by the state and sold directly to the consumer, increasing purity. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Much of this revenue may be attributed to people who became addicted before they were aware of the negative health consequences. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
